text:
Celebrations, Parades and Municipal Events: A set of two views showing the Black Elks marching northward on Seventh Ave. past West 125th Street. The photographer's vantage point is at West 126th Street in No. 1 and at West 127th Street in No. 2, viewing south-westward to show buildings on the west side of the Avenue. The large 12 story structure seen is the Hotel Theresa, which occupies the entire block front from 124th to 125th Streets.
Decoration Day Parade
May 30, 1931.
George L. Balgue.
title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal events - Decoration Day Parade.

Manhattanville: Dr. John E. Ferdinand home at No. 230 West 125th Street, south side, west of Seventh Ave. Today (1937) this site is included in the lot upon which stands L.M. Blumstein's Department Store, No. 230-244 West 125th Street. Dr. Ferdinand resided here between 1880 and 1887 having lived (according to Phillip's Elite Directory) in the years 1874-1875 at No's. 29, 31, 35 West 127th Street.

Unknown date.
